reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars love this dresser! it’s perfect for the price!!
reviews.reviewText: this dresser is bigger medium sized dresser give off ikea vibes for sure. it is about $40 cheaper for me since an ikea is a a few hours away. i highly recommend getting this desser. although i just bought it so we have yet to see how it holds up. it’s perfect in size to put smaller items in it like socks, underwear, etc. i love the modern look. lastly it’s not the best of the best quality. to be exact it not made with sturdy wood but it’s very nice. if you take care of it and aren’t rough, it seems like it should last you awhile. putting together isn’t complicated either and the process takes a few hours if not more if you have adhd like me lol. it was relaxing matter of fact, just put on some music and get to work!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy Assembly and Perfect Fit
reviews.reviewText: My concern about these types of cabinets is whether the drawers are really going to fit well as I've had some that required tons of adjustments. I bought two of these and all 10 drawers fit absolutely perfectly and all parts were in order with a few spares of each.I think each one took me between 2-3 hours to assemble but I don't move as quickly as I used to and I wish I had a high table or bench to work with as that would greatly easy assembly vs. crawling around on the floor like I had to do. These were to put in a closet that had very limited depth so they work perfectly. I will say the drawers are a bit shallow and wish I had more deeper drawers (for things like jeans) but can't complain too much as this was a perfect fit and easy assembly with not that many separate pieces of hardware.I didn't use any of the safety stuff because I have no little children in my home and in an apartment so can't drill into the walls anyway.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It’s a cute dresser, looks like the pictures but a little on the smaller size. It did take some time to put together being that I did it by myself. The directions are good and easy to follow. A drill is needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My husband and I put this together in under an hour and it’s perfection. I was worried by the mixed reviews but happy to took a chance. He’s very handy so I knew if anyone could master the build it’s him. It’s for our 4 month olds room 🥰 *black dresser*

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: No es la mejor calidad pero se ve resistente para el precio. Luce increíble y Lo que más me gusto es el tamaño (pequeño), porque era Justo lo q necesitaba. Y las gavetas para ser pequeñas tienen buen espacio. Fíjense en las medidas antes de comprar.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This dresser came in like 5000 pieces and was a pain to assemble. That's all fine, but it stinks so bad! There is this horrible chemical smell coming off of it. I've let it air out for two weeks now and it STILL STINKS! In order to return it I'd have to take it all apart and pay for return shipping. That's ridiculous! I shouldn't have to pay to return a dresser that the small makes me gag.Do not buy this unless you want your house to smell like chemicals 🤢

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Ok for the price, with a few modifications
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble, but a little flimsy, especially the drawer slides. I added a 3" 3/4 plywood strip to the top back (to bridge the sides, (4) 90 degree cabinet triangle brackets to the top, changed out the drawer slides to 14" soft close, added 7" bar cabinet handle pulls, and drawer dividers, which improved it substantially for a cost of about $80. The product has a chemical smell that lasted for 2 months before it went away. The drawers are only 4" deep, which is good to store socks, underwear, rolled up yoga pants, or kids clothes, but not many large pieces of clothing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but fits a lot of clothes
reviews.reviewText: It looks simple but elegant, fits all of my workout clothes and shirts. I would get two of them just so it can look bigger.Took about 2 hours to assembly but I was also by myself. After having it for 2 months the shelves because a little loose.
